# Technical Explanation Guidelines

## Concept Introduction

- Start with a high-level overview before diving into details
- Define new concepts with clear, concise language
- Relate new concepts to familiar ones when possible
- Use analogies to explain complex or abstract ideas
- Provide real-world applications of theoretical concepts
- Include visual representations for complex concepts
- Address "why" before "how" for better conceptual understanding

